Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Cut the @sweet potato{2} widthways into 1cm thick rounds (no need to peel).

Put the sweet potato onto a large #baking tray{} and sprinkle over the @Central American style spice mix{1%sachet}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, bake on the middle shelf until golden and cooked through, ~{25-28%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, drain the @sweetcorn{160%grams} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the heat if necessary. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice colour. Transfer the sweetcorn to a medium #bowl{} and set aside.

While the corn is frying, quarter the @baby plum tomatoes{125%grams}. Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out onto a board. Cut into 1cm chunks.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Halve the @lime{2}(halved). Halve the @red chilli{1} lengthways, deseed, then finely chop.

Lay the @sea bream fillets{2} skin-side up, onto a lined baking tray. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

When the sweet potatoes have 10 mins remaining, bake the sea bream on the top shelf until the fish is cooked, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, give the (now empty) frying pan a quick wipe clean.

Drain the @king prawns{150%grams}. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in the frying pan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the prawns. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and stir-fry for ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the garlic and chilli (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. They're cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Remove the pan from the heat. Add half the lime juice, half the coriander and the @sugar{1%tsp}. Stir to combine.

When everything's nearly ready, add the tomatoes and avocado to the bowl of charred corn.

Add the remaining coriander, remaining lime juice and the @olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp}.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Stir to combine.

> Pantry for sugar and olive oil amounts: 1 tsp sugar and 1 tbsp olive oil for the dressing.

Share the sea bream between your plates and spoon over the prawns and any sauce from the pan.

Serve the sliced sweet potatoes and sweetcorn salsa on the side.

Crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50%grams} over the sweet potatoes to finish.

Enjoy!